We translated the presence or absence of NPI, or public health restrictions, into a parameter that reduces agents’ infectivity. This indicator, λNPI, can range between 0 (no restrictions, λmin) and a maximum value, λmax. It modifies the individual probability to infect as follows:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
