				\begin{document}$$ P_{\inf } = P_{\inf ,0} \cdot \left( {1 - \lambda_{NPI} \left( t \right)} \right), $$\end{document}Pinf=Pinf,0·1-λNPIt,where Pinf,0 is the individual probability to infect in the absence of restrictions. λNPI can acquire different values during the simulation, accounting for periods with and without NPI. The level of NPI can be determined from the situation in hospitals, which would activate or release measures in an automated manner (see Supplementary material 1 for details on this sub-model).
